♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.191 --> 01:47.107
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:54.375 --> 01:56.464
BAYWATCH

02:02.948 --> 02:07.997
[ORCHESTRAL MUSIC PLAYING]

02:18.616 --> 02:23.621
[SULTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

03:55.278 --> 03:57.846
LOS ANGELES COUNTY LIFEGUARD
BAYWATCH

04:12.730 --> 04:14.602
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS WEATHER?

04:14.732 --> 04:15.864
IT'S 9:00 IN THE MORNING,

04:15.994 --> 04:17.648
ALREADY IT'S SWELTERING OUT.

04:17.779 --> 04:20.781
IT'S THE SANTA ANA WINDS
BLOWING HOT FROM THE EAST.

04:20.911 --> 04:22.262
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS,
DON'T YOU?

04:22.392 --> 04:23.611
NO, WHAT?

04:23.741 --> 04:26.483
IT MEANS ALL THE WEIRDOS
GET BLOWN TO THE BEACH.

04:33.621 --> 04:34.535
MITCH!

04:34.665 --> 04:36.014
MITCH, THERE YOU ARE.

04:36.145 --> 04:37.538
I'VE BEEN LOOKING EVERYWHERE
FOR YOU.

04:37.668 --> 04:38.626
GUESS WHO'S HERE.

04:38.756 --> 04:40.062
-WHO?
-GUESS.

04:40.192 --> 04:42.543
C.J., I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS. WHO?

04:42.673 --> 04:43.457
WHO'S HERE?

04:43.587 --> 04:44.371
[SCREAMING]

04:44.501 --> 04:45.589
[LAUGHING]

04:45.720 --> 04:47.722
-HI.
-DESTINY.

04:48.462 --> 04:50.377
GOD, IT'S SO GOOD
TO FEEL YOUR AURA AGAIN.

04:50.507 --> 04:52.422
WHAT BRINGS YOU BACK
TO BAYWATCH?

04:52.553 --> 04:55.033
WELL, I KIND OF THOUGHT
YOU SHOULD BE FOREWARNED.

04:55.164 --> 04:56.644
FOREWARNED OF WHAT?

04:56.774 --> 04:59.603
THE ASTROLOGICAL ALIGNMENT,
IT'S A VERY RARE OCCURRENCE.

04:59.734 --> 05:02.519
YEAH, YEAH, FIRST
THERE'S A FULL MOON RISING,

05:02.650 --> 05:05.043
WHICH AS YOU KNOW TENDS
TO MAKE THE FEMALES AWRY

05:05.174 --> 05:06.697
AND UNPREDICTABLE.

05:06.828 --> 05:09.091
LIKE THE TIDES OF THE SEA.

05:09.221 --> 05:10.571
YOU KNOW WHAT,
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THIS--

05:10.701 --> 05:13.269
THEN, THERE'S
A 90 DEGREE DESCENT ON MARS,

05:13.400 --> 05:15.576
WHICH TENDS TO MAKE THE MALES
VERY AGGRESSIVE.

05:15.706 --> 05:16.925
VERY.

05:17.055 --> 05:18.883
BUT THE CRAZY THING IS
THERE'S ALL THESE COMETS

05:19.014 --> 05:20.450
CRASHING ON JUPITER.

05:20.581 --> 05:21.886
I MEAN, WHO KNOWS WHAT KIND
OF CHAOS THIS COULD BRING.

05:23.366 --> 05:26.587
MY ADVICE TO YOU IS TO SLAP
AN EXTRA LAYER OF SUNSCREEN

05:26.717 --> 05:29.459
ON YOUR SOUL, IT COULD GET
REALLY INTENSE OUT THERE.

05:29.590 --> 05:31.766
THANK YOU. THANK YOU BOTH
FOR SHARING THAT WITH ME.

05:31.896 --> 05:33.071
BUT YOU KNOW, I'VE GOT TO GO.

05:33.202 --> 05:36.074
I'M DUE BACK ON PLANET EARTH
IN TEN MINUTES.

05:36.205 --> 05:38.686
OH, WELL THINK PEACE.

05:44.735 --> 05:47.521
HEY MAN, I HOPE
THE ICE DOESN'T MELT.

05:49.218 --> 05:50.828
HEY GUYS.

05:50.959 --> 05:52.569
HAVE YOU GOT ENOUGH BEER THERE?

05:54.005 --> 05:56.399
DUDE, I TOLD YOU
WE SHOULD'VE BROUGHT MORE.

05:57.574 --> 05:59.271
I WAS BEING FACETIOUS.

05:59.968 --> 06:01.448
[CHUCKLING]

06:01.578 --> 06:03.406
NOW, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO TAKE
THAT BEER BACK TO THE CAR

06:03.537 --> 06:04.668
OR THE POLICE WILL MAKE
YOU POUR IT OUT.

06:04.799 --> 06:06.148
OH, NO WAY DUDE.

06:06.278 --> 06:07.715
I SAW THOSE ON TV COMMERCIALS,

06:07.845 --> 06:09.804
THEY'RE ALWAYS DRINKING BEER
ON THE BEACH.

06:09.934 --> 06:12.241
NOT AN L.A. COUNTY BEACH.
NO ALCOHOL HERE.

06:13.068 --> 06:14.374
BUMMER!

06:14.504 --> 06:16.071
YEAH, BOGUS.

06:16.637 --> 06:19.074
YOU GUYS REALLY BELIEVE
WHAT YOU SEE ON TV?

06:27.038 --> 06:28.475
HEY THERE, MITCH.

06:28.605 --> 06:29.824
HI.

06:32.130 --> 06:33.349
DO I KNOW YOU?

06:34.176 --> 06:35.046
YEAH.

06:35.177 --> 06:36.483
FROM WHERE?

06:36.613 --> 06:39.181
WELL THAT'S FOR ME TO KNOW
AND FOR YOU TO FIND OUT.

06:39.834 --> 06:40.965
WHY DON'T YOU THINK ABOUT IT
FOR A WHILE.

06:41.096 --> 06:42.750
I'LL BE AROUND.

06:44.795 --> 06:50.279
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

07:08.428 --> 07:10.908
[HUMMING]

07:14.956 --> 07:16.740
HEY, WHAT KIND OF TAROT DECK
IS THAT?

07:16.871 --> 07:17.872
OH, IT'S UM--

07:18.002 --> 07:18.916
SUMERIAN.

07:19.047 --> 07:20.440
WHAT'S IT FOR?

07:20.570 --> 07:22.137
WE NEED A LEADER.

07:22.267 --> 07:24.487
AND THE TOP CARD
IN THE PYRAMID

07:24.618 --> 07:25.967
SHOULD GIVE US A SIGN.

07:26.097 --> 07:27.316
YEAH, WE'RE LIKE--

07:27.447 --> 07:28.926
WE'RE TRYING TO GET
AS MANY PEOPLE AS POSSIBLE

07:29.057 --> 07:31.015
TO MEDITATE
ON PEACE CONSCIOUSNESS

07:31.146 --> 07:32.756
FOR SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA.

07:32.887 --> 07:34.410
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

07:35.019 --> 07:37.282
IF ENOUGH PEOPLE THINK PEACE,
IT COULD HAPPEN.

07:44.115 --> 07:48.337
WHOA, THAT'S
A HIGH PRIESTESS CARD.

07:48.468 --> 07:49.469
11 THE HIGH PRIESTESS

07:51.688 --> 07:53.211
WOW!

07:56.040 --> 07:57.389
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

07:57.520 --> 07:58.565
YOU'RE OUR LEADER.

08:02.003 --> 08:03.526
GEE, I WOULD REALLY LOVE
TO HELP,

08:03.657 --> 08:05.572
BUT I HAVE TO WORK TODAY.

08:05.702 --> 08:08.313
THAT'S OKAY, WE UNDERSTAND.

08:08.444 --> 08:11.099
BUT, COULD YOU JUST
HELP SPREAD GOOD VIBES?

08:11.229 --> 08:12.666
I WILL.

08:15.016 --> 08:16.670
WHOA.

08:48.092 --> 08:49.137
CAN I HELP YOU?

08:49.267 --> 08:50.573
THAT'S A JOKE.

08:51.966 --> 08:52.923
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

08:53.054 --> 08:54.446
YEAH, SOMETHING'S WRONG.

08:54.577 --> 08:56.884
I WANT YOU OUT OF MY LIFE.
I CAN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE!

08:58.929 --> 09:00.235
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

09:00.365 --> 09:02.019
I'M TALKING ABOUT KIM.

09:02.150 --> 09:04.718
HOW ARE WE SUPPOSED TO BE HAPPY
WITH YOU MESSING IT ALL UP?

09:04.848 --> 09:06.458
I THINK YOU'RE A LITTLE CONFUSED
HERE, PAL.

09:06.589 --> 09:07.547
WHY DON'T YOU JUST CALM DOWN?

09:07.677 --> 09:08.896
DON'T TELL ME TO CALM DOWN!

09:09.026 --> 09:10.593
YOU CALM DOWN, MR. RIPPLE PECS!

09:12.160 --> 09:13.640
AND LEAVE US ALONE!

09:16.251 --> 09:17.948
MR. RIPPLE PECS?

09:19.994 --> 09:21.561
GOTTA BE THE WIND.

09:27.436 --> 09:30.091
HEY, MISTER! I FOUND
THIS IN THE WATER.

09:31.396 --> 09:32.267
WHERE?

09:32.397 --> 09:33.311
OVER THERE.

09:35.270 --> 09:37.011
-DUDE, YEAH, YEAH!
-HOLD IT, GUYS.

09:37.141 --> 09:38.578
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THIS.

09:42.494 --> 09:43.583
HEY, EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.

09:47.935 --> 09:49.501
CAN I THROW THIS TO YOU?

09:54.419 --> 09:56.073
COULD I BRING YOU A BLANKET?

10:01.818 --> 10:02.819
WHAT SHOULD WE DO?

10:08.172 --> 10:09.478
I NEED THIS.

10:16.441 --> 10:19.531
[BEACH COMMOTION]

10:45.253 --> 10:48.517
HEY! HEY! STOP IT.

10:48.648 --> 10:50.824
STOP IT, RIGHT NOW.
KNOCK IT OFF.

10:50.954 --> 10:52.129
JUST STOP.

10:54.915 --> 10:55.959
AMY!

10:56.525 --> 11:01.269
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

11:02.966 --> 11:03.924
AMY

11:12.367 --> 11:15.849
HELP, PLEASE! HELP!

11:15.979 --> 11:17.198
AMY.

11:20.854 --> 11:23.813
AMY! AMY!

11:26.294 --> 11:29.166
PLEASE, PLEASE, MY DAUGHTER.

11:29.297 --> 11:30.646
-WHAT HAPPENED?
-SHE'S GONE UNDER.

11:30.777 --> 11:32.300
-OKAY, CALM DOWN. CALM DOWN.
-SHE'S DROWNING.

11:32.430 --> 11:33.257
WHERE? WHERE?

11:33.388 --> 11:35.085
SHE'S RIGHT OUT THERE!

11:35.216 --> 11:37.044
PLEASE, JUST GET HER!
SHE'S DROWNING.

11:38.262 --> 11:40.090
I'M GLAD I COULD'VE
BEEN OF SERVICE.

11:40.221 --> 11:42.049
WOULDN'T WANT YOU
TO CATCH A COLD.

11:48.403 --> 11:52.973
[EXCITING MUSIC PLAYING]

13:07.047 --> 13:08.004
SEE ANYTHING?

13:09.005 --> 13:09.963
NO.

14:05.583 --> 14:06.933
WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:07.063 --> 14:09.152
WE HAVE A SUBMERSION,
BUT WE CAN'T EVEN SPOT HER.

14:09.283 --> 14:10.458
GIVE ME SPARE AIR!

14:10.588 --> 14:11.894
ALL RIGHT, HOLD ON.

14:13.330 --> 14:14.549
HERE YOU GO.

14:26.430 --> 14:30.870
[SIRENS BLARING]

14:32.567 --> 14:34.221
ALL RIGHT,
START CLEARING THE WATER.

14:35.222 --> 14:36.658
ANYBODY SEE WHAT HAPPENED?

14:36.788 --> 14:38.312
STAND BACK, PLEASE.

14:38.442 --> 14:40.662
THAT MAN OVER THERE,
SAID HIS DAUGHTER WAS DROWNING.

14:40.792 --> 14:41.924
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TAKE OVER.

14:42.055 --> 14:43.621
GO BACK AND COVER YOUR WATER.

14:46.102 --> 14:47.669
EXCUSE ME, SIR,
I'M LIEUTENANT BUCHANNON.

14:47.799 --> 14:49.018
CAN YOU TELL ME EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED?

14:49.149 --> 14:50.280
LOOK, I CAN'T DO THIS NOW,
PLEASE.

14:50.411 --> 14:51.978
ALL RIGHT, I CAN'T TALK
TO YOU LIKE THIS.

14:54.067 --> 14:54.850
I UNDERSTAND--

14:54.981 --> 14:56.417
JUST FIND HER FOR ME, PLEASE!

14:56.547 --> 14:58.636
I UNDERSTAND, SIR, BUT WE CAN DO
A MUCH MORE EFFICIENT JOB

14:58.767 --> 15:00.334
IF YOU JUST HELP US A LITTLE.

15:00.464 --> 15:02.031
LOOK, WHAT ELSE IS IT
THAT YOU NEED TO KNOW?

15:02.162 --> 15:03.467
SHE WENT UNDER, SHE'S DROWNING.

15:03.598 --> 15:04.425
WHO?

15:04.555 --> 15:05.687
MY LITTLE GIRL.

15:05.817 --> 15:06.644
WHAT'S HER NAME?

15:06.775 --> 15:08.037
AMY.

15:08.168 --> 15:09.560
AND YOUR NAME?

15:09.691 --> 15:10.648
-SIR?
-WHAT?

15:10.779 --> 15:11.911
I NEED YOUR NAME.

15:13.260 --> 15:14.261
BILL COOPER.

15:15.305 --> 15:17.525
MR. COOPER,
CAN YOU TELL ME VERY CAREFULLY

15:17.655 --> 15:18.830
EXACTLY WHAT HAPPENED?

15:19.788 --> 15:22.660
SHE WAS SWIMMING
RIGHT OUT THERE.

15:22.791 --> 15:25.054
-ALONE?
-YES, ALONE.

15:26.273 --> 15:27.491
WHAT WAS SHE WEARING?

15:27.622 --> 15:28.928
SHE WAS SWIMMING ALONE.

15:29.798 --> 15:31.626
SHE MUST'VE GOTTEN TIRED.

15:35.282 --> 15:36.631
SHE WENT UNDER.

15:37.980 --> 15:39.764
WHAT WAS SHE WEARING?

15:39.895 --> 15:42.463
SHE'S WEARING A BATHING SUIT,
WHAT ELSE?

15:42.593 --> 15:43.464
AND WHAT COLOR?

15:43.594 --> 15:44.508
IT'S RED.

15:44.639 --> 15:46.206
IT WAS RED, JUST LIKE YOURS.

15:46.815 --> 15:48.077
AND HOW OLD IS SHE?

15:48.208 --> 15:49.383
SHE'S 12.

16:06.052 --> 16:08.706
THE VISIBILITY IS PERFECT.
I DON'T GET IT.

16:08.837 --> 16:10.534
-WE SHOULD'VE FOUND HER BY NOW.
-YOU KEEP LOOKING.

16:10.665 --> 16:12.449
THE UNDERCURRENT
MUST'VE CARRIED HER AWAY.

16:12.580 --> 16:15.409
CAROLINE,
DID YOU SEE HER GO UNDER?

16:15.539 --> 16:16.453
NO.

16:22.633 --> 16:23.678
EH.

16:23.808 --> 16:26.028
[SUSPICIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

16:37.170 --> 16:39.085
MR. COOPER, I KNOW
THIS IS DIFFICULT FOR YOU,

16:39.215 --> 16:41.348
BUT PLEASE,
WOULD YOU TRY AND HELP US?

16:41.478 --> 16:43.785
WHY DO YOU KEEP BOMBARDING ME
WITH QUESTIONS?

16:43.915 --> 16:45.308
WHAT ELSE DO YOU NEED TO KNOW?

16:45.439 --> 16:47.354
DID ANYBODY ELSE COME
TO THE BEACH WITH YOU TODAY?

16:47.963 --> 16:49.095
-NO.

16:49.225 --> 16:51.010
IS IT POSSIBLE THAT AMY
WASN'T IN TROUBLE?

16:52.707 --> 16:54.448
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

16:54.578 --> 16:56.885
THE WATER IS VERY CROWDED.

16:57.668 --> 16:59.627
YOU'RE VERY FAR AWAY,
MAYBE SHE SWAM UNDERWATER,

16:59.757 --> 17:01.411
AND CAME UP SOME PLACE ELSE.

17:01.542 --> 17:02.586
WHERE ELSE?

17:05.241 --> 17:07.548
LOOK AT THE BEACH, DON'T YOU
THINK SHE WOULD BE HERE?

17:07.678 --> 17:08.940
MAYBE SHE WENT UP TO THE PIER.

17:09.070 --> 17:11.421
THIS IS RIDICULOUS!

17:11.551 --> 17:13.989
SHE DID NOT GO UP TO THE PIER!

17:16.644 --> 17:18.733
LOOK, I'VE GOT TO FILE
A MISSING PERSON'S REPORT.

17:18.863 --> 17:19.733
WHY?

17:19.864 --> 17:20.909
IT'S JUST ROUTINE.

17:21.040 --> 17:21.910
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

17:48.589 --> 17:49.894
WE'VE JUST BEEN CALLED IN.

17:50.591 --> 17:52.419
WHAT? I'M NOT QUITTING!

17:52.549 --> 17:54.421
WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF OCEAN,
CAROLINE.

17:55.074 --> 17:56.640
LOOK, GIVE ME MORE SPARE AIR!

17:56.771 --> 17:59.165
NO! MITCH CALLED OFF THE RESCUE.

17:59.295 --> 18:00.731
WE GOTTA DO WHAT HE SAYS.

18:08.739 --> 18:13.657
[MYSTICAL PERCUSSION MUSIC]

18:16.791 --> 18:21.883
[LAUGHING]

18:24.625 --> 18:25.843
HELLO?

18:27.802 --> 18:29.108
EXCUSE ME.

18:31.066 --> 18:32.502
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

18:34.069 --> 18:36.898
OH, I'M SORRY,
THIS IS A PUBLIC BEACH,

18:37.028 --> 18:38.073
YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED
TO DO THAT HERE.

18:38.204 --> 18:40.206
OH, IT'S NOW OR NEVER, HONEY.

18:40.336 --> 18:43.078
SO GO AHEAD AND CALL
THE VICE SQUAD IF YOU WANT.

18:43.209 --> 18:44.688
THERE'S A REALLY NICE HOTEL

18:44.819 --> 18:46.081
ABOUT A BLOCK
AND A HALF DOWN THE STREET.

18:46.212 --> 18:48.518
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

18:48.649 --> 18:49.954
THERE'S SOMETHING IN THE AIR.

18:50.085 --> 18:52.392
HE HASN'T BEEN ABLE
TO DO THIS FOR YEARS.

18:52.522 --> 18:54.176
NO, I DO UNDERSTAND.

18:54.307 --> 18:56.483
THERE'S A WHOLE SERIES OF COSMIC
CONVERSIONS HAPPENING

18:56.613 --> 18:58.006
FROM COMETS RUSHING INTO
JUPITER

18:58.137 --> 18:59.921
TO THE SANTA ANA WINDS.

19:00.051 --> 19:02.141
IT'S STIRRING UP A LOT
OF REAL UNUSUAL ENERGY,

19:02.271 --> 19:03.577
BUT WE NEED TO HARNESS
THAT ENERGY

19:03.707 --> 19:04.621
FOR THE GOOD OF MANKIND.

19:04.752 --> 19:06.841
IT DON'T GET
NO GOODER THAN THIS.

19:23.727 --> 19:25.251
YOU AGAIN?

19:28.863 --> 19:30.604
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP HERE?

19:30.734 --> 19:32.606
JUST THOUGHT I'D KEEP AN EYE
ON YOUR STAND FOR YOU.

19:32.736 --> 19:34.303
YEAH, WELL YOU CAN'T BE UP HERE,
YOU GOTTA--

19:37.567 --> 19:38.394
WHO ARE YOU?

19:39.047 --> 19:40.527
YOU REALLY DON'T REMEMBER?

19:41.528 --> 19:43.530
I HAVEN'T HAD THAT MUCH TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT,

19:43.660 --> 19:44.966
SO WHY DON'T YOU GIVE ME A HINT.

19:45.575 --> 19:49.057
ALL RIGHT, I WAS OUT HERE
FROM PARIS ON SUMMER VACATION.

19:49.188 --> 19:50.189
PARIS?

19:50.319 --> 19:51.625
PARIS, TEXAS.

19:51.755 --> 19:54.062
AND I WAS TRYING TO LEARN
HOW TO WATER SKI,

19:54.193 --> 19:58.066
AND SOMEHOW I GOT ALL TIED UP
IN THE LINES AND I WENT UNDER.

19:58.806 --> 20:00.547
NEVER THOUGHT I'D COME
BACK UP AGAIN.

20:01.200 --> 20:03.898
THEN SUDDENLY, THERE YOU WERE,

20:05.465 --> 20:07.728
BREATHING LIFE RIGHT BACK
INTO MY LUNGS.

20:08.381 --> 20:09.904
I WOKE UP LIKE SLEEPING BEAUTY

20:10.034 --> 20:11.340
WHEN SHE GOT KISSED
BY THE PRINCE.

20:11.949 --> 20:14.604
YOU KNOW SOMETHING,
I REMEMBER THAT RESCUE.

20:17.041 --> 20:18.086
IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

20:18.217 --> 20:19.174
11 YEARS.

20:20.044 --> 20:21.916
AND YOU CAME ALL THE WAY
OUT HERE TO THANK ME?

20:22.046 --> 20:24.484
WELL, I DIDN'T COME OUT HERE
JUST TO THANK YOU.

20:24.614 --> 20:25.920
I CAME OUT HERE TO BE WITH YOU.

20:28.052 --> 20:29.706
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BE WITH ME?

20:29.837 --> 20:33.232
WELL, I'M ENGAGED
AND I JUST NEED TO KNOW

20:33.362 --> 20:35.321
IF I'M SELLING MYSELF SHORT
BY MARRYING ALBERT.

20:35.451 --> 20:36.713
ALBERT?

20:37.975 --> 20:39.934
ALBERT. WAIT A MINUTE,
IS YOUR NAME KIM?

20:40.064 --> 20:42.110
-YEAH.
-YOU'RE ENGAGED TO HIM?

20:42.241 --> 20:43.459
YEAH.

20:43.590 --> 20:45.983
I NEVER STOPPED THINKING
ABOUT YOU THOUGH.

20:46.114 --> 20:48.421
FIRST, I THOUGHT IT WAS A
SCHOOLGIRL CRUSH OR SOMETHING,

20:48.551 --> 20:51.380
BUT AS I'VE GROWN OLDER
MY FEELINGS

20:51.511 --> 20:52.773
HAVE JUST GOTTEN STRONGER.

20:53.382 --> 20:57.038
LOOK, YOU HAVE BUILT THIS THING
WAY OUT OF PROPORTION.

20:57.168 --> 21:00.346
I STILL DON'T KNOW
IF I LOVE ALBERT FOR HIMSELF,

21:00.476 --> 21:02.348
OR IF IT'S JUST
BECAUSE HE LOOKS LIKE YOU.

21:02.478 --> 21:04.045
YOU THINK HE LOOKS LIKE ME?

21:04.175 --> 21:06.439
BUT HE'S VERY DIFFERENT INSIDE,
THOUGH.

21:06.569 --> 21:08.092
HE'S NOT BRAVE LIKE YOU.

21:08.702 --> 21:11.270
HE DOESN'T HAVE
THAT SAME HEROIC PRESENCE.

21:12.183 --> 21:16.187
WHEN YOU GET RIGHT DOWN TO IT,
HE'S BASICALLY A WIMP.

21:16.971 --> 21:22.237
LOOK, KIM,
YOU ARE INCREDIBLY BEAUTIFUL,

21:22.368 --> 21:24.239
AND I AM VERY FLATTERED

21:24.370 --> 21:27.198
BUT I WON'T GET IN THE MIDDLE
OF YOUR RELATIONSHIP.

21:27.329 --> 21:30.289
WELL, MITCH, YOU ALREADY ARE.

21:49.220 --> 21:51.310
WHY DID YOU CALL OFF THE RESCUE?

21:52.528 --> 21:54.095
CAROLINE,
YOU'VE BEEN SEARCHING THE WATER

21:54.225 --> 21:55.792
FOR OVER TWO HOURS.

21:55.923 --> 21:58.491
I QUESTIONED PEOPLE ON THE BEACH
WHO NEVER GOT ANY CONFIRMATION

21:58.621 --> 22:00.536
THAT SHE WAS EVEN IN THE WATER.
I TALKED TO THE FATHER

22:00.667 --> 22:02.190
WHO DIDN'T GIVE ME
A STRAIGHT STORY.

22:02.321 --> 22:04.279
WHEN THE POLICE SHOWED UP,
HE TOOK OFF.

22:04.410 --> 22:05.976
NOT ONE SINGLE PERSON
ON THE BEACH

22:06.107 --> 22:08.675
EVEN SAW A LITTLE GIRL
WITH THAT MAN.

22:08.805 --> 22:10.938
SO I MADE THE DECISION
TO CALL OFF THE SEARCH.

22:11.068 --> 22:12.548
WELL IT WAS THE WRONG DECISION.

22:12.679 --> 22:15.334
CAROLINE,
I REALIZE YOU FEEL RESPONSIBLE.

22:15.464 --> 22:17.292
I CANNOT HAVE YOU
OUT ON THE WATER

22:17.423 --> 22:19.120
CHASING AFTER SOME PHANTOM.

22:19.816 --> 22:21.818
NOW I NEED YOU
TO GO BACK TO YOUR TOWER,

22:21.949 --> 22:24.038
AND GET CONTROL
OF YOUR EMOTIONS, OKAY?

22:24.734 --> 22:25.648
OKAY.

22:29.348 --> 22:34.396
-MMMMMM
-MMMMMM

22:34.527 --> 22:35.832
WOW, THIS IS FANTASTIC,

22:35.963 --> 22:37.486
YOU REALLY HAVE EVERYBODY
THINKING PEACE.

22:37.617 --> 22:39.358
YEAH, WE HAVE TO KEEP IT UP
UNTIL MIDNIGHT.

22:39.488 --> 22:40.837
I MEAN, L.A. IS SO BIG,

22:40.968 --> 22:42.926
IT NEEDS THE HELP IT CAN GET
ON A DAY LIKE TODAY.

22:45.799 --> 22:48.323
UH-OH, HERE COMES
TINY TIM AGAIN.

22:50.194 --> 22:52.327
HE LOVES HIS HEAVY METAL.

22:54.198 --> 22:56.984
USUALLY,
AT ABOUT 1,000 DECIBELS.

22:57.811 --> 22:59.769
OH, I'D BETTER GO
TAKE CARE OF THIS.

22:59.900 --> 23:01.554
-KEEP THINKING PEACE.
-OKAY.

23:01.684 --> 23:03.860
AND GET OUT YOUR EARPLUGS.

23:03.991 --> 23:06.559
[VIOLIN MUSIC PLAYING]

23:21.182 --> 23:22.618
I'M NOT LETTING YOU TAKE HER!

23:22.749 --> 23:23.793
[CHUCKLING]

23:23.924 --> 23:25.665
ALBERT,
I DON'T WANT TO TAKE HER.

23:25.795 --> 23:27.493
ARE YOU JUST GONNA USE HER
AND THROW HER AWAY?

23:27.623 --> 23:29.103
I'M NOT GONNA THROW HER AWAY.

23:29.233 --> 23:30.409
ARE YOU GONNA ADD HER
TO YOUR BEACH HAREM,

23:30.539 --> 23:31.714
IS THAT IT, MR. RIPPLE PECS?

23:31.845 --> 23:33.977
STOP WITH THE MR. RIPPLE PECS,
HUH?

23:34.108 --> 23:35.544
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

23:35.675 --> 23:38.155
YOU'RE BIGGER THAN ME,
YOU'RE STRONGER THAN ME,

23:38.286 --> 23:40.070
BUT I'M FIGHTING
FOR A GOOD CAUSE.

23:40.201 --> 23:42.769
AND I'VE GOT SOMETHING
THAT YOU DON'T HAVE.

23:42.899 --> 23:44.161
WHAT?

23:44.292 --> 23:45.293
SPUNK.

23:47.208 --> 23:49.428
SPUNK IS GOOD, IT'S GOOD.

23:49.558 --> 23:51.560
SPUNK IS GOOD. IT'S GOOD.

23:52.300 --> 23:54.345
COME ON, LET'S GET
THIS OVER WITH.

23:54.476 --> 23:56.130
TO THE DEATH, WINNER GETS KIM.

23:56.260 --> 23:57.740
I DON'T WANT KIM.

23:57.871 --> 23:59.481
OH, NOW SHE'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH
FOR YOU, IS THAT IT?

23:59.612 --> 24:02.310
TO THE DEATH! TO THE DEATH!

24:05.052 --> 24:06.183
[PANTING]

24:06.314 --> 24:09.752
OKAY, TO THE PAIN. TO THE PAIN.

24:09.883 --> 24:11.754
CAN I LET GO OF YOU NOW?

24:11.885 --> 24:13.060
OKAY.

24:14.017 --> 24:15.584
ALL RIGHT, CALM DOWN.

24:15.715 --> 24:18.108
ALL RIGHT? ALL RIGHT.

24:19.109 --> 24:21.155
THE WAY I SEE,
YOU'VE GOT A SERIOUS PROBLEM.

24:21.285 --> 24:22.722
MAYBE I CAN HELP YOU.

24:23.418 --> 24:25.855
SHE WANTS YOU
TO BE MORE LIKE ME, RIGHT?

24:25.986 --> 24:27.683
EVERYTHING I DO, SHE CRITICIZES.

24:27.814 --> 24:29.032
"MITCH WOULDN'T DO THAT.

24:29.163 --> 24:31.208
NO, MITCH WOULD DO IT THIS WAY."

24:31.339 --> 24:33.863
SHE'S CONSTANTLY COMPARING ME
TO YOU.

24:34.385 --> 24:35.909
SHE THINKS YOU'RE THE GREATEST.

24:36.039 --> 24:38.477
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
ANYTHING MORE ABSURD?

24:40.479 --> 24:42.393
IF SHE WON'T ACCEPT YOU
FOR THE PERSON YOU ARE,

24:42.524 --> 24:43.917
MAYBE YOU'RE NOT
WITH THE RIGHT WOMAN.

24:44.047 --> 24:46.006
I LOVE HER
MORE THAN LIFE ITSELF.

24:46.136 --> 24:47.703
IF SHE WANTS ME
TO BE MORE LIKE YOU,

24:47.834 --> 24:49.618
THEN I HAVE TO LEARN HOW.

24:58.322 --> 25:03.545
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

25:13.207 --> 25:17.777
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

25:20.431 --> 25:25.480
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

25:28.396 --> 25:31.225
♪ YOU CAN'T HAVE
PLEASURE WITHOUT PAIN ♪

25:32.400 --> 25:34.837
♪ WON'T WIN THE GIRL
UNLESS YOU TRAIN ♪

25:36.360 --> 25:38.711
♪ TIME TO LEARN
IT'S BACK TO SCHOOL ♪

25:40.060 --> 25:42.889
♪ STRIP IT DOWN
AND LEARN THE RULES ♪

25:43.019 --> 25:48.024
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

25:50.984 --> 25:55.684
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

