26:09.916 --> 26:12.483
♪ THIS COULD BE
THE DEATH OF ME ♪

26:14.007 --> 26:16.966
♪ PAY NO MIND
THEY STOP AND STARE ♪

26:17.793 --> 26:20.448
♪ GET THE GROOVE
THEY WON'T COMPARE ♪

26:20.579 --> 26:25.714
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

26:28.108 --> 26:33.330
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

26:36.203 --> 26:38.031
♪ SOMETIMES IT'S NOT YOUR DAY

26:38.161 --> 26:39.902
♪ STAND UP AND WASH YOUR FACE

26:40.033 --> 26:42.078
♪ ALL CLEAR
AND SOON YOU'LL SEE ♪

26:42.209 --> 26:43.950
♪ NOW LOOK ALL EYES ON ME

26:44.080 --> 26:45.865
♪ TAKE NOTES
TIL YOU GOT IT DOWN ♪

26:45.995 --> 26:47.431
♪ THUMBS UP
WHEN THERE'S GIRLS AROUND ♪

26:47.562 --> 26:49.608
♪ HEADS UP
CAUSE WE'RE MOVING FAST ♪

26:49.738 --> 26:52.436
♪ IT'S TIME FOR THE MASTER CLASS JUST WATCH ♪

26:58.442 --> 27:03.491
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

27:06.320 --> 27:10.716
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

27:13.414 --> 27:18.462
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

27:20.987 --> 27:25.600
♪ OH I...
WANNA BE COOL LIKE YOU ♪

27:39.222 --> 27:40.267
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

27:41.311 --> 27:42.486
YEAH.

27:44.097 --> 27:45.881
CAROLINE,
NOBODY DROWNED HERE TODAY.

27:46.012 --> 27:47.317
HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?

27:47.448 --> 27:49.493
BELIEVE ME, IF THAT MAN'S
LITTLE GIRL HAD DROWNED,

27:49.624 --> 27:50.581
HE WOULDN'T HAVE JUST VANISHED.

27:50.712 --> 27:52.279
IT JUST DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

27:53.062 --> 27:54.673
NOTHING MAKES SENSE TODAY.

27:54.803 --> 27:56.718
C.J., WHY WOULD HE MAKE UP
A STORY LIKE THAT?

27:56.849 --> 27:57.980
BECAUSE HE HAS A PROBLEM.

27:58.111 --> 27:59.982
FOR SOME REASON,
HE'S TAKING IT OUT ON US.

28:01.723 --> 28:03.290
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

28:03.420 --> 28:04.683
YOU DID YOUR JOB.

28:05.422 --> 28:07.163
IF STEPHANIE WERE HERE, SHE'D BE
TELLING YOU THE SAME THING.

28:07.294 --> 28:08.861
OKAY LOOK,
I APPRECIATE IT YOU TRYING

28:08.991 --> 28:10.514
TO MAKE ME FEEL BETTER,
I REALLY DO.

28:10.645 --> 28:13.126
C.J., I JUST KIND OF WANNA BE
ALONE FOR A WHILE, IS THAT OKAY?

28:13.256 --> 28:14.301
OKAY.

28:16.216 --> 28:17.173
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

28:17.304 --> 28:18.522
YEAH.

28:19.132 --> 28:20.394
THEN I'LL SEE YOU BACK
AT HEADQUARTERS.

28:20.524 --> 28:21.700
OKAY.

28:25.138 --> 28:26.269
AMY!

28:27.096 --> 28:28.619
AMY!

28:28.750 --> 28:30.056
AMY?

28:31.057 --> 28:32.406
AMY!

28:36.976 --> 28:39.065
AMY!

28:43.809 --> 28:49.118
[EXCITING MUSIC PLAYING]

28:56.604 --> 28:58.693
DADDY'S COMING!

29:01.565 --> 29:03.611
I'LL SAVE YOU!

30:18.120 --> 30:22.951
[SIRENS BLARING]

30:38.097 --> 30:43.363
[PANTING AND GRUNTING]

30:58.987 --> 31:00.423
HE'S GOT A PULSE.

31:00.554 --> 31:01.860
HE'S NOT BREATHING.

31:10.520 --> 31:12.696
[COUGHING]

31:13.306 --> 31:14.829
OKAY, OKAY.

31:16.831 --> 31:18.180
OKAY.

31:18.311 --> 31:20.182
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

31:20.313 --> 31:21.531
STAY STILL.

31:23.316 --> 31:24.752
IT'S OKAY.

31:27.189 --> 31:28.712
HE'S IN SHOCK.

31:28.843 --> 31:30.714
MITCH, GET A BLANKET
FROM THE BACK OF THE TRUCK.

31:30.845 --> 31:32.716
-GOT IT.
-IT'S OKAY.

31:33.587 --> 31:35.197
IT'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

31:38.244 --> 31:39.636
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

31:47.688 --> 31:50.082
IT'S OKAY. YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

31:54.303 --> 31:55.391
SO I CALLED HIS WIFE.

31:56.915 --> 31:58.264
HIS DAUGHTER DID DROWN.

31:58.873 --> 32:00.005
WHAT?

32:00.135 --> 32:02.529
SHE DROWNED A YEAR AGO,
C.J., IN FLORIDA.

32:03.051 --> 32:04.357
THEY MOVED OUT HERE
TO TRY AND FORGET,

32:04.487 --> 32:06.054
BUT HE CAN'T JUST SEEM
TO GET OVER IT.

32:06.185 --> 32:07.534
DOES HE HAVE ANY OTHER CHILDREN?

32:07.664 --> 32:09.884
YEAH, HE DOES. HE HAS A SON
AND A YOUNGER DAUGHTER.

32:38.608 --> 32:39.740
AMY?

32:40.480 --> 32:43.265
NO. NO, MY NAME'S CAROLINE.

32:43.396 --> 32:45.398
I'M THE LIFEGUARD
WHO BROUGHT YOU IN.

32:48.053 --> 32:49.706
I HEARD ABOUT YOUR DAUGHTER,
MR. COOPER.

32:49.837 --> 32:50.794
I'M SO SORRY.

32:55.190 --> 32:56.539
I TALKED TO YOUR WIFE.

32:56.670 --> 32:58.193
AND SHE TOLD ME YOU HAVE
A VERY WONDERFUL FAMILY AT HOME.

32:58.324 --> 32:59.194
YOU'RE VERY LUCKY.

33:01.066 --> 33:02.458
I DON'T FEEL VERY LUCKY.

33:02.589 --> 33:03.982
I KNOW.

33:05.113 --> 33:06.723
I'M SORRY, THAT WAS
A REALLY STUPID THING TO SAY.

33:06.854 --> 33:09.422
I GUESS I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO SAY--

33:11.511 --> 33:14.383
YOU HAVE TWO CHILDREN
AT HOME WHO LOVE YOU

33:14.514 --> 33:15.950
AND NEED YOU SO VERY MUCH.

33:17.734 --> 33:18.779
I MISS AMY.

33:21.260 --> 33:23.392
I MISS HER SO MUCH.

33:27.440 --> 33:28.963
I CAN'T FORGET HER.

33:29.703 --> 33:31.270
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO FORGET HER.

33:32.619 --> 33:34.534
BUT I THINK
YOU NEED TO LET HER GO.

33:38.277 --> 33:41.236
I CAN'T TELL YOU ANYTHING THAT'S
GONNA MAKE THIS ALL RIGHT,

33:41.367 --> 33:42.542
AND I CAN'T BE YOUR DAUGHTER.

33:47.721 --> 33:49.244
BUT I CAN BE YOUR FRIEND.

34:07.001 --> 34:08.089
ALBERT.

34:10.222 --> 34:11.527
SHE DIDN'T GO FOR IT, HUH?

34:12.092 --> 34:14.574
SHE SAID SHE DIDN'T WANT
A MITCH BUCHANNON WANNABE.

34:14.704 --> 34:16.228
SHE WANTED THE REAL THING.

34:16.358 --> 34:18.360
SOUNDS LIKE IT'S TIME
FOR PLAN B.

34:19.927 --> 34:21.320
WHAT'S PLAN B?

34:21.449 --> 34:24.583
I SHATTER HER IMAGE OF ME,
SHE LOSES HER INFATUATION,

34:24.714 --> 34:27.021
AND REALIZES THAT YOU ARE
THE MAN OF HER DREAMS.

34:27.152 --> 34:29.284
YEAH RIGHT,
AND HOW ARE YOU GONNA DO THAT?

34:31.808 --> 34:34.550
[ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING]

34:34.681 --> 34:39.902
♪ SHE LIKES ME JUST FOR ME

34:54.179 --> 34:56.964
♪ DON'T CALL ME CRAZY
I'M JUST AHEAD ♪

34:57.094 --> 34:58.270
♪ OF THE TIMES

35:01.925 --> 35:03.579
♪ PRETEND I'M LAZY

35:03.710 --> 35:05.712
♪ I'LL MAKE HER LOSE HER MIND

35:08.889 --> 35:11.674
♪ SOME WOULD SAY SHE LIKES ME

35:11.805 --> 35:13.111
♪ JUST FOR ME

35:15.852 --> 35:20.466
♪ BLOWN AWAY
SHE LIKES ME JUST FOR ME ♪

35:23.817 --> 35:27.864
♪ OBNOXIOUS SUITOR
I'M NOT A GENTLEMAN ♪

35:31.433 --> 35:34.654
♪ SO MAKE IT RUDER
ALL CHIVALRY IS DEAD ♪

35:38.310 --> 35:41.008
♪ SOME WOULD SAY SHE LIKES ME

35:41.139 --> 35:42.618
♪ JUST FOR ME

35:46.056 --> 35:50.148
♪ BLOWN AWAY
SHE LIKES ME JUST FOR ME ♪

35:52.541 --> 35:57.546
♪ SHE LIKES ME JUST FOR ME

36:23.224 --> 36:25.661
♪ SOME WOULD SAY SHE LIKES ME

36:25.792 --> 36:27.359
♪ JUST FOR ME

36:30.362 --> 36:34.627
♪ BLOWN AWAY
SHE LIKES ME JUST FOR ME ♪

37:01.001 --> 37:04.047
MITCH, I DON'T REALLY KNOW
HOW TO SAY THIS.

37:05.832 --> 37:09.618
OVER THE YEARS, I'VE THOUGHT
ABOUT YOU ALL THE TIME,

37:09.749 --> 37:13.231
ABOUT HOW YOU SAVED ME,
HOW HEROIC YOU ARE.

37:13.840 --> 37:16.495
I CREATED A FANTASY
WITHOUT EVEN KNOWING YOU.

37:16.625 --> 37:19.802
AND NOW, THAT YOU'VE SEEN ME.

37:20.238 --> 37:26.200
WELL, I THINK YOU'RE BETTER
THAN I EVER DREAMED OF.

37:26.766 --> 37:29.856
I MEAN, NOT ONLY ARE YOU STRONG
AND HEROIC AT THE BEACH,

37:29.986 --> 37:32.467
BUT ALONE WITH A WOMAN
YOU'RE JUST BOYISH AND CLUMSY,

37:32.598 --> 37:34.426
AND IT'S SO SWEET.

37:35.514 --> 37:37.559
I JUST COULDN'T ASK
FOR ANYTHING MORE.

37:37.690 --> 37:41.128
[PLEASANT MUSIC PLAYING]

37:48.788 --> 37:50.920
LOOK, KIM, WE NEED TO TALK.

37:51.051 --> 37:52.226
THIS IS SO GREAT.

37:52.357 --> 37:53.749
HEY, MITCH,
WHEN DO YOU GET VACATION,

37:53.880 --> 37:55.577
BECAUSE I WANT YOU TO COME
BACK TO PARIS, TEXAS WITH ME.

37:55.708 --> 37:56.535
NO, I DON'T WANT--

37:56.665 --> 37:57.840
NO, NOT TO LIVE, SILLY.

37:57.971 --> 37:59.320
I JUST WANT YOU TO COME SEE
WHERE I'M FROM,

37:59.451 --> 38:00.930
AND MEET MY FAMILY
AND EVERYTHING.

38:01.061 --> 38:02.323
KIM, THAT'S
WHAT I'M TRYING TO TELL YOU.

38:02.454 --> 38:04.325
YOU ARE SO WONDERFUL.

38:04.456 --> 38:06.022
AND YOU'RE JUST
SO WILD AND CRAZY.

38:12.681 --> 38:13.900
ALBERT?

38:14.030 --> 38:15.336
LISTEN, I--

38:15.467 --> 38:16.772
IT'S OKAY, MITCH, I UNDERSTAND.

38:18.339 --> 38:20.950
KIM, I LOVE YOU VERY MUCH,

38:21.081 --> 38:22.865
AND I'M SORRY
THAT I WASN'T THE ONE FOR YOU,

38:22.996 --> 38:24.911
BUT YOUR HAPPINESS
IS THE MOST IMPORTANT THING

38:25.041 --> 38:25.955
IN THE WORLD FOR ME.

38:26.086 --> 38:28.088
AND I WISH YOU THE BEST OF LUCK.

38:28.218 --> 38:29.785
YOU'RE GETTING A GREAT GUY.

38:34.094 --> 38:36.096
MITCH, TAKE CARE OF HER.

38:36.226 --> 38:37.358
SHE'S ONE IN A MILLION.

38:40.318 --> 38:42.320
AND SHE'S GETTING ONE
IN A MILLION IN ME.

38:43.495 --> 38:46.324
I MEAN, WHY SHOULD SHE SETTLE
FOR A HAMBURGER LIKE YOU,

38:46.454 --> 38:49.544
WHEN SHE COULD HAVE
STEAK LIKE ME.

38:51.285 --> 38:52.765
COME HERE, BABY.

38:52.895 --> 38:54.114
OH, BABY.

38:54.897 --> 38:56.986
WHAT DID YOU SEE
IN THAT SQUIRT, ANYWAY?

38:57.117 --> 39:00.076
I MEAN I COULD UNDERSTAND YOU
WANTING AN IMITATION MITCH,

39:00.207 --> 39:01.730
EVERY WOMAN SHOULD HAVE ONE,

39:02.644 --> 39:05.125
BUT YOU DON'T SHOP
FOR ONE AT A GARAGE SALE.

39:05.255 --> 39:07.475
HOW CAN YOU BE SO RUDE?

39:07.606 --> 39:09.129
YO! FLAT BUTT.

39:09.259 --> 39:11.958
CINCH UP THAT BELT,
YOUR PANTS MIGHT FALL DOWN.

39:12.088 --> 39:14.395
AND INSENSITIVE!

39:14.526 --> 39:16.266
OH, I'M JUST SOWING
MY OATS HERE.

39:16.397 --> 39:18.399
YOU KNOW, I RESCUED A FINE WOMAN

39:18.530 --> 39:20.575
FROM DROWNING
IN A DULL MARRIAGE.

39:20.706 --> 39:24.100
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME,
YOU BULLY!

39:26.059 --> 39:27.626
ALBERT, WAIT.

39:29.845 --> 39:31.020
[SIGHING]

39:31.151 --> 39:32.892
CAN YOU EVER FORGIVE ME?

39:33.022 --> 39:34.546
OF COURSE I FORGIVE YOU.

39:39.638 --> 39:40.987
LET'S GO HOME.

40:07.013 --> 40:07.927
HI.

40:09.015 --> 40:10.103
HI.

40:11.626 --> 40:13.585
I JUST WANTED TO APOLOGIZE AGAIN

40:13.715 --> 40:15.151
FOR THE WAY I ACTED TODAY.

40:15.761 --> 40:17.415
I DON'T USUALLY FLY OFF
THE HANDLE LIKE THAT.

40:18.024 --> 40:19.286
FORGET ABOUT IT.

40:19.417 --> 40:20.418
IT HAPPENS TO THE BEST OF US.

40:22.768 --> 40:24.291
MITCH, DO YOU THINK
I HAVE WHAT IT TAKES

40:24.422 --> 40:25.292
TO BE A LIFEGUARD?

40:25.423 --> 40:26.380
OR AM I JUST KIDDING MYSELF?

40:28.643 --> 40:30.253
I THINK YOU'VE GOT ALL THE TOOLS

40:30.384 --> 40:31.690
TO BE A VERY GOOD LIFEGUARD.

40:31.820 --> 40:34.040
BUT IN THIS JOB,
YOU'VE GOTTA PROVE YOURSELF

40:34.170 --> 40:35.128
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

40:35.737 --> 40:38.479
BELIEVE ME, IT'S A NONSTOP
LEARNING EXPERIENCE.

40:41.090 --> 40:42.396
HEY GUYS.

40:42.527 --> 40:43.702
HI, GUYS.

40:44.920 --> 40:46.269
WHERE'S DESTINY?

40:47.140 --> 40:48.663
SHE'S STILL OUT THERE
THINKING PEACE.

40:50.056 --> 40:51.927
WELL, I GUESS SHE GOT
THE MESSAGE ACROSS,

40:52.058 --> 40:53.146
WE ALL SURVIVED A DAY

40:53.276 --> 40:55.148
WITHOUT MAJOR TRAUMAS
TO OUR SOULS.

40:55.278 --> 40:56.454
I HOPE.

40:57.672 --> 40:59.413
WELL I ALL CAN THINK
ABOUT RIGHT NOW

40:59.544 --> 41:02.068
IS GETTING UNDER A NICE,
COLD SHOWER.

41:02.416 --> 41:04.244
THEN WHY DON'T YOU GO
DOWNSTAIRS?

41:04.374 --> 41:05.985
BECAUSE I'M TOO TIRED TO MOVE.

41:06.551 --> 41:07.900
DO YOU FEEL THAT?

41:09.989 --> 41:11.164
FEEL WHAT?

41:12.121 --> 41:14.689
THE WIND COMING OFF THE WATER.

41:14.820 --> 41:15.951
SO?

41:16.822 --> 41:20.086
ONSHORE FLOW,
MEANS NO MORE SANTA ANA WINDS.

41:21.261 --> 41:22.958
OH GOD, THAT DOES FEEL GOOD.

41:23.611 --> 41:25.178
WELL, WE'RE NOT OUT
OF THE WOODS YET.

41:25.308 --> 41:26.614
THE CONVERGENCE LASTS
'TIL MIDNIGHT,

41:26.745 --> 41:28.616
SO WE STILL HAVE TO THINK PEACE.

41:35.928 --> 41:39.928
[ENDING MUSIC]
